WEBVTT

00:00:01.970 --> 00:00:08.689
This is a proclamation or a declaration by a group of Levites. It was done. They made this proclamation

00:00:08.689 --> 00:00:16.929
or really a prayer to Jehovah after the wall around Jerusalem had been rebuilt back in 455 BCE.

00:00:16.929 --> 00:00:25.730
And this is what was said. You are Jehovah, the true God, who chose Abraham and brought him out

00:00:25.730 --> 00:00:33.409
of Ur of the Caldians and gave him the name Abraham. You found his heart faithful before you,

00:00:33.969 --> 00:00:40.369
so you made a covenant with him to give him the land of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites,

00:00:40.369 --> 00:00:47.649
the Parasites, the Jebiusites, and the Gurgishites. Then it says, to give it to his offspring,

00:00:48.289 --> 00:00:56.450
and you kept your promises because you are righteous. And that's interesting that last statement,

00:00:56.450 --> 00:01:03.250
how is righteousness or Jehovah's righteousness connected to Israel becoming his chosen people?

00:01:04.930 --> 00:01:11.409
They didn't, as a people, really merit it or deserve it, but the point is Jehovah honored

00:01:12.209 --> 00:01:19.650
his promise to Abraham. And that's why Jehovah is declared righteous by the Levites. They

00:01:19.650 --> 00:01:25.650
recognized that it was due to a promise made to their forefather that they were chosen by God as

00:01:25.650 --> 00:01:32.609
his nation, his people, and that he gave them the promised land. But the thing is that the idea

00:01:32.609 --> 00:01:37.730
of carrying out your words, that latter part there, or the second half of the scripture, and you

00:01:37.730 --> 00:01:43.890
proceeded to carry out your words because you are righteous. And that's what people do, people

00:01:43.890 --> 00:01:51.730
who are righteous, who have self-respect and who honor their promises. And Jehovah God expects us

00:01:52.849 --> 00:01:58.769
to always be true to our word, to honor our promises. Now, that's not easy to do. Sometimes

00:01:58.769 --> 00:02:04.769
we'll find ourselves in a situation where it may be quite difficult to follow through and honor

00:02:04.769 --> 00:02:10.610
our word. But consider what Jesus said. Remember the scripture at Matthew 5, 37.

00:02:12.289 --> 00:02:18.289
Just let your word yes, mean yes. You're no, no. But then that interesting addition

00:02:18.930 --> 00:02:25.250
for what goes beyond these is from the wicked one. But we know who the wicked one is. It's Satan

00:02:25.250 --> 00:02:32.449
the devil. And his goals were deception and disruption. Satan had no intention of fulfilling what

00:02:32.449 --> 00:02:37.729
he promised, Eve. In fact, he was incapable. He couldn't fulfill it. He told her, you will not die.

00:02:39.009 --> 00:02:45.250
That was a bald lie right from the beginning. And he was unable to comply with what he said.

00:02:46.050 --> 00:02:49.889
And isn't that true? There are people like that today. They'll tell you things. They'll promise

00:02:49.889 --> 00:02:58.289
things. But they have no intention of fulfilling them. And those who do that are under the influence

00:02:58.370 --> 00:03:05.009
of Satan the devil. There are things that we say yes to. There are promises that we make that we

00:03:05.009 --> 00:03:14.129
don't want to break. And foremost is our our vow, our promise, our dedication to serve Jehovah forever.

00:03:15.090 --> 00:03:20.689
We say yes three times. The watchtower pointed that out. It was interesting. We say yes when we

00:03:22.289 --> 00:03:27.250
are interviewed by an elder to become an unbaptized publisher. We say yes, I want to be a Jehovah's

00:03:27.250 --> 00:03:35.330
witness. And then we say yes again when we go over the questions for baptism that we've dedicated

00:03:35.330 --> 00:03:41.009
our life to Jehovah and we want to serve him. We believe what the Scriptures teach. We want to

00:03:41.009 --> 00:03:47.009
give our life to our God. And then the third time we say yes when we're at the assembly, usually it's

00:03:47.009 --> 00:03:54.930
an assembly where the baptism talk is given and we answer the questions and say yes. And we make

00:03:54.930 --> 00:04:00.689
a public declaration of our dedication to Jehovah God. So we put our hand to the plow.

00:04:01.810 --> 00:04:09.969
We don't want to take our hand off the plow. We promised to fulfill our dedication vow, our promise

00:04:09.969 --> 00:04:15.250
in this regard. And really that helps make us righteous in a sense, not self-righteous. That's

00:04:15.250 --> 00:04:20.610
disgusting to God. But righteous in that we're we have self-respect. We're honoring our word. We want to

00:04:20.610 --> 00:04:27.170
honor our great God, Jehovah. There's another yes that we say that we want to be loyal to.

00:04:27.970 --> 00:04:34.610
That's the yes when we take the marriage vow. They should not be broken. The marriage vow is,

00:04:35.170 --> 00:04:42.529
it's interesting about vows. Usually vows are vows require us to do something. It's not that we

00:04:42.529 --> 00:04:47.569
get something when we make a vow. But usually if we make a vow it's because we're going to do

00:04:47.569 --> 00:04:53.569
something and that's the way it is with the marriage vow. It's to do things, to obey, to love,

00:04:53.569 --> 00:04:59.730
to cherish, for a wife it's to respect deeply. But the marriage vow has more to do with giving

00:05:00.370 --> 00:05:06.050
